Task 1: Create Visual Threat Models in Draw.io
Step 1: Access Draw.io and Set Up Workspace
Open Firefox browser:
firefox &
Navigate to https://app.diagrams.net/
Click Create New Diagram → Blank Diagram
Name your diagram: ecommerce_threat_model
Step 2: Design System Architecture
Create a basic e-commerce application architecture:

Add Components (from General shapes library):

User Browser (rectangle, label: "User Browser")
Web Server (rectangle, label: "Web Server")
Database (cylinder shape, label: "Customer DB")
Payment API (rectangle, label: "Payment Gateway")
Connect Components (use Connector tool):

User Browser → Web Server (HTTP/HTTPS)
Web Server → Database (SQL queries)
Web Server → Payment API (API calls)
Add Trust Boundaries (use dashed rectangles):

External Zone: User Browser
DMZ: Web Server
Internal Zone: Database
Third-party: Payment API
Step 3: Document Threats
Add text boxes near each connection with potential threats:

User → Web: "SQL Injection, XSS, CSRF, Session Hijacking"
Web → DB: "Privilege Escalation, Data Breach, Unauthorized Access"
Web → Payment: "MITM, API Key Exposure, Data Interception"
