Task 2: Map Attack Paths with MITRE ATT&CK Navigator
Step 1: Access MITRE ATT&CK Navigator
Open new browser tab: https://mitre-attack.github.io/attack-navigator/
Click Create New Layer → Enterprise matrix
Familiarize yourself with:
Tactics: Attack stages (columns)
Techniques: Specific attack methods (cells)
Color coding: Customize to show threat severity
Step 2: Create Attack Scenario
Map a web application compromise scenario:

Initial Access: Select T1190 (Exploit Public-Facing Application)
Execution: Select T1059.007 (JavaScript)
Persistence: Select T1505.003 (Web Shell)
Privilege Escalation: Select T1068 (Exploitation for Privilege Escalation)
Credential Access: Select T1555 (Credentials from Password Stores)
Collection: Select T1005 (Data from Local System)
Exfiltration: Select T1041 (Exfiltration Over C2 Channel)
Step 3: Customize and Export
For each selected technique:

Right-click → Set Technique State → Enabled
Change color to red for critical threats
Add comments describing the attack step
Export the layer:

Layer Controls → Download Layer
Save as ecommerce_attack_layer.json
Document attack narrative in Layer Information section

